summary:
With a love for puzzels and riddles I am very happy with my current PhD position in Operation Research at Maastricht University. I am mainly working on uniqueness and computation of Nash equilibria in atomic splittable congestion games. Here matroids and polymatroids turn out to be particular interesting concepts. 

Besides my research I like to teach, play board games or cards, hike, travel, dance, and maintaining a tiny garden on our balcony. 

I am happy to answer any questions.

Here we taught teachers from high schools and primary schools how to incorporate computers in their school system. The problem is that many companies help schools by donating hardware. The schools we visited have the hardware they need, but did not know how to use it. We taught them about hardware, open source software and the Microsoft office programs. We cooperated with 12 students from Kampala University.\n\n"}]
